The death of another person pf the four who allegedly engaged in a foursome–three men and a lady— at a student lodge on Tuesday.
The Police said they were all students of the Federal University of Technology, Owerri, said that substances suspected to be Tramadol tablets and Indian hemp were found in the hostel were two out of the four students died on Tuesday.
Commissioner of Police, Rabiu Ladodo, who confirmed the death of the third student, Aka Uche,  urged parents to discourage their children from taking to drugs.

“I just got the information today (Thursday) that he has died. He died in the hospital were he was admitted,’ he said.
“His death has increased to three the number of persons who died from the incident.
“The girl among them, Onyinyechi Okafor, is alive and I learnt that her condition is stable.”
The authorities of the Federal University of Technology, Owerri, said they were investigating to ascertain if the four persons were their students.

			
